xpected web resource patterns. The Java run on existing coverage failed, and I've realized that there's no need for new dependencies or Docker configurations to resolve this assertion failure. Just adding more dependencies won't fix the underlying problem. It's crucial to pinpoint what exactly went wrong instead of complicating things with unnecessary additions.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra dependency, Docker image, environment variable, or system property is needed for the current spring-test coverage; the reported failure appears to be a Spring 7 behavior/assertion mismatch in AOT resource hint patterns, not missing setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"spring-test exposes many optional integration areas such as Servlet mocks, MockMvc, WebFlux, Mockito, TestNG, HtmlUnit, and SQL support; if generated tests expand into those areas they may require additional optional dependencies, but they are not needed for the existing failing coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_03a2ec468f4cd75e016a28cb46bdec8196b8b79e4ba5cf05af\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 630, "output": 1614, "cacheRead": 43008, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 45252, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781058341115, "responseId": "resp_03a2ec468f4cd75e016a28cb25c1e0819694f412d9fad7119b"}, "toolResults": []}
